Record Class OrderDTO

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.cafe.backend.dto.OrderDTO
Record Components:
id - The unique identifier of the order.
discount - The applied discount in percentage; typically 0 when creating a new order.
readyPickupTime - The expected pickup time for the order; required during order creation.
status - The current status of the order; typically set to PROCESSING on creation.
tip - The optional tip amount provided by the user; 0.0 by default.
cafeteriaId - The ID of the cafeteria where the order was placed.
userId - The ID of the user who created the order.
totalPrice - The total calculated price for the order, including discounts and tip.
orderProducts - A list of OrderProductDTO representing the individual products in the order.
public record OrderDTO(Long id, int discount, LocalDateTime readyPickupTime, OrderStatusEnum status, double tip, Long cafeteriaId, Long userId, double totalPrice, List<OrderProductDTO> orderProducts) extends Record
The OrderDTO is a Data Transfer Object used to represent order data exchanged between the backend and frontend.

It encapsulates information about the order, such as its status, discount, pricing details, associated user and cafeteria, and the list of products within the order.
